# ============================================================
# SECURITY CORE POLICY
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: policy
domain: security
scope: security.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines policy constraints for security.

## policy_rules
Security policy constrains:
- which sensitive paths require verification
- how masked output is handled
- who may see security detail
- when security paths must be denied or escalated

## required_behavior
- verification scope must be explicit
- masking scope must be explicit
- disclosure scope must be explicit
- denial behavior must be explicit

## disclosure_matrix
- bounded public security summary
- operator-scoped detail
- reviewer detail
- historical security detail
- denied output

## allowed_denied_matrix
- allow sensitive action only for valid verified scope
- allow disclosure only for allowed actors
- deny hidden privilege widening
- deny disclosure beyond allowed scope

## escalation_rules
If security context,
verification basis,
masking scope,
or disclosure scope is unclear,
the security path must stop and escalate.

## review_checklist
- verification policy is explicit
- masking policy is explicit
- disclosure matrix exists
- denial behavior is explicit
